<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="466" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1772,1977]" pageId="3" pageNumber="466">Eight males and two females of this taxon were collected on the hilltop of the PNSD in 2014. All specimens were observed from mid-afternoon to sunset, flying from two to four meters above the ground.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1772,1977]" pageId="3" pageNumber="466">
The phenotype of the specimens found at the PNSD is similar to the type specimen of 
<taxonomicName authority="Warren et al. 2016" authorityName="Warren et al." authorityYear="2016" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="466" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nepticula" subSpecies="stigmosa">
<emphasis box="[1185,1435,1844,1869]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="466">M. nepticula stigmosa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Warren" box="[158,382,1880,1905]" pageId="3" pageNumber="466" refString="Warren, A. D., Davis, K. J., Stangeland, E. M., Pelham, J. P. &amp; Grishin, N. V. (2016) Illustrated lists of American butterflies (North and South America). Available from: http: // butterfliesofamerica. com / L / Neotropical. htm (accessed 23 May 2016)" type="journal article" year="2016">
Warren 
<emphasis box="[252,311,1880,1905]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="466">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName box="[661,916,1880,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="466" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nepticula" subSpecies="stigmosa">
<emphasis box="[661,916,1880,1905]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="466">M. nepticula stigmosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Bates, 1868" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1868" box="[1074,1345,1880,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="466" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis box="[1074,1199,1880,1905]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="466">M. simplex</emphasis>
Bates, 1868
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Hall &amp; Lamas, 2007" authorityName="Hall &amp; Lamas" authorityYear="2007" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Mesene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="466" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leucogyna">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="466">M. leucogyna</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hall" box="[276,516,1916,1941]" pageId="3" pageNumber="466" refString="Hall, J. P. W. &amp; Lamas, G. (2007) Four new symmachiine taxa from the eastern Andes of Peru and Ecuador (Lepidoptera: Riodinidae). Zootaxa, 1533, 41 - 52." type="journal article" year="2007">Hall &amp; Lamas, 2007</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; these three species probably are closely related, belonging to the same species group (
<bibRefCitation author="Hall" box="[231,459,1952,1977]" pageId="3" pageNumber="466" refString="Hall, J. P. W. &amp; Lamas, G. (2007) Four new symmachiine taxa from the eastern Andes of Peru and Ecuador (Lepidoptera: Riodinidae). Zootaxa, 1533, 41 - 52." type="journal article" year="2007">Hall &amp; Lamas 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
